org.apache.juneau.jena

Class RdfParserSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.juneau.Session
      • org.apache.juneau.parser.ParserSession
        • org.apache.juneau.jena.RdfParserSession

  • public class RdfParserSession
extends ParserSession
    Session object that lives for the duration of a single use of RdfParser.

    This class is NOT thread safe. It is meant to be discarded after one-time use.

    Author:
    James Bognar (james.bognar@salesforce.com)

    • Constructor Detail

      • RdfParserSession

        protected RdfParserSession(RdfParserContext ctx,
                           BeanContext beanContext,
                           Object input,
                           ObjectMap op,
                           Method javaMethod,
                           Object outer)
        Create a new session using properties specified in the context.
        Parameters:
        ctx - The context creating this session object. The context contains all the configuration settings for this object.
        beanContext - The bean context being used.
        input - The input. Can be any of the following types:
        • null
        • Reader
        • CharSequence
        • InputStream containing UTF-8 encoded text.
        • File containing system encoded text.
        op - The override properties. These override any context properties defined in the context.
        javaMethod - The java method that called this parser, usually the method in a REST servlet.
        outer - The outer object for instantiating top-level non-static inner classes.

      • decodeString

        public final String decodeString(Object o)
        Decodes the specified string.

        If RdfParserContext.RDF_trimWhitespace is true, the resulting string is trimmed before decoding.

        If ParserSession.isTrimStrings() is true, the resulting string is trimmed after decoding.

        Parameters:
        o - The string to trim.
        Returns:
        The trimmed string, or null if the string was null.
